cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper deals with deep neural network frameworks for age and gender classification using profile face and ear images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves multimodal learning, which makes it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of deep learning techniques and domain adaptation suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with soft biometric traits, which could be relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the use of image-based classification suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
